        <title>Center Body General Description</title>
        
        <levelledPara>
          <title>Overview</title>
          <para>
            The Center Body is the primary structural component of the fuselage.
          </para>
          <para>
            The AMPEL360 AIR-T uses a Blended Wing Body (BWB) configuration.
          </para>
          <para>
            The Center Body gives the main load-bearing structure.
          </para>
          <para>
            It contains these critical systems:
          </para>
          <para>
            - Passenger cabin
          </para>
          <para>
            - Cargo areas
          </para>
          <para>
            - Flight control systems
          </para>
          <para>
            This data module is part of program 02-AIR-TRANSPORT.
          </para>
          <para>
            The segment is PAX_AIRBORNE.
          </para>
          <para>
            The configuration is BWB-H2-Hy-E version Q100.
          </para>
        </levelledPara>
        
        <levelledPara>
          <title>Key Features</title>
          <para>
            The Center Body connects with the wing structures.
          </para>
          <para>
            This connection makes the BWB aerodynamic profile.
          </para>
          <para>
            The structure uses advanced composite materials.
          </para>
          <para>
            Aluminum alloy reinforcements are at critical load points.
          </para>
